[SN]TITLE[SN]
West Midlands Police officer charged with rape

[SN]FIRST-SENTENCE[SN]
A West Midlands Police officer has been charged with rape.

[SN]RESTBODY[SN]
PC Ben Clay is due to appear at Dudley Magistrates Court on Wednesday where he will be formally charged.
The 39-year-old was arrested after a woman made the allegation on 28 January 2015. The alleged offence happened while the officer was off-duty.
PC Clay, a neighbourhood police officer, was suspended from his position at Wolverhampton police station following his arrest.
